10:
I think we're in the clear now. We'll
escort you to the city, just in case.
16:
Still, you kill one and another pops
up. Is this normal for the Farlands?
20:
Hardly. We shouldn't be seeing
hordes of monsters so large that
villagers need to flee their homes.
And the nobles are standing idly by...
26: Lord's Aegis! The people need us!
29:
Your Highness! Don't rush in by
yourself! My poor heart cannot
stand it!
37: Let the light pierce my foes! Go forth!
40: Ugh! Is my power alone not enough?!
53:
Those are the Nouin Knights! And
that's the royal treasure, the
legendary...
55:
Are you from the royal family of
Nialas?
65:
Yuwel Nouin! The great hero of the
Swallow Knights! The rumors were
true! You really survived!
73:
Of course! Five years ago, the
Swallow Knights fought in unison to
protect the people, despite
everything! True knights, through
and through!
77:
Nouin Knights! Your... No, OUR hero
has returned, just in time to save us
from calamity!
81:
W-wait! I'm not sure I'm following
you!
86:
I cannot believe you left me behind
to fight by yourselves! How could
you?
90:
W-wait, what? Prince Varen?! What
are you doing here?
94:
Oh, Libram! You came back as well!
As you can see, I'm just doing my
part to protect the people. Don't
worry, I have Azrail's permission!
103:
Indeed. This is Varen Nialas, the
crown prince, whose family we Swes
are sworn to protect!
107:
I'm so glad you came, Yuwel! I'm
overjoyed, really!
111:
Which reminds me, we have no time
to lose here! We must let everyone
know that the hero Yuwel is back!
Let's go!
116:
Are you sure you don't know the
guy? He moves just like you.
121:
I'm certain I've never met him
before, but you have a point. That
was a Nouin sword technique...
124:
What does he mean when he says
that I am... a hero?
129:
Thank you, everyone, for gathering
here. Welcome to the home of the
Swes.
132:
Thank you for protecting His
Highness too. You also spared me
the trouble of introducing you to
each other, although this is not the
outcome I was expecting...
137:
Yuwel, what foods do you like?
Where do you live? Who taught you
how to fight? How come you still
look so young?!
142:
Your Highness, if I may. We have
more pressing business to attend
to...
145:
The reason I summoned you here is
simple. I will not mince words. Things
are bad, and the usual infighting
does not help.
153:
Ah, right... You and your friend are
from Palpebra. Some explanation is
in order.
156:
The Farlands is divided into ten
territories. One ruled directly by His
Majesty the King, and nine by noble
houses which have sworn loyalty to
him.
158:
Each of the Nine Houses has its own
duty to uphold.
163:
The sixth house, House Swes, is in
charge of foreign diplomacy! Azrail
fulfilled this role well by reducing our
tensions with Palpebra. But, for
problems like the one we have now...
167:
That would be the jurisdiction of the
Nouins, the ninth house. Our mission
is to protect peace and maintain
order, as well as to manage
soldiers...
171:
However, House Nouin alone can
only do so much. Ideally, we would
have already submitted a proposal
to the council offering our support...
174:
But some are against this. Namely
the Kweturs of the fourth house, and
the Oxtans of the eighth house.
179:
That sounds like infighting all right.
But why are they against it?
182:
Because of our relationship with
Palpebra. We believe that our only
way to survive is to call for their help.
185:
However, those two houses worry
that Palpebra will take this chance
to conquer us, and that we should
save our forces to fend them off
should that happen.
188:
They even went so far as to suggest
that Palpebra is behind this surge of
monsters. We would have better
luck talking to a wall.
193:
Five years have passed, but nothing
has changed. What would Palpebra
stand to gain by doing something
like that?!
199:
Exactly! That's what I'm trying to
make them see! And that is why I
summoned you here!
202:
Palpebra isn't our enemy, and I want
everyone to understand that!
206:
Come with me, Yuwel! We'll speak
with the Nine Houses!
210:
Your Highness... With all due respect,
I am not in the position to influence
your kingdom's politics.
213:
The people believe that I died after
fleeing my country. I am no longer
considered a knight, but a deserter.
217: But are you not a Swallow Knight?
221:
One whose only desire is to protect
the people? As a true knight your
words will have no problem getting
through those thick skulls!
224: Won't you come with me, Yuwel?
233:
In that case... I suggest you visit
Ciel... I mean, the House of Tris.
236:
You save him just like you did me
during the peace treaty ceremony.
And I understand that his younger
sister Celtie is a friend of yours.
238:
I do not know if speaking with him
will improve the situation, but at the
very least it's unlikely to make it
worse.
242:
As you say, Ciel is the most likely to
at least listen to us...
247:
Then, it's decided! We'll go to the
House of Tris. We'll persuade them
first!
251:
Good luck! I'll be waiting here, of
course. That man is frightening
when angered, and I'd rather not
take the chance!
255:
Let's go. I don't know how useful I'll
prove to be, Your Highness, but I will
accompany you nonetheless.
